<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+b|</b>&gt; The Office of DPL is a quite demanding and important role in</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+c|</b>&gt; Debian. It is also very much under-used, underestimated and largely</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+d|</b>&gt; reduced to be a figure head.</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+e|</b>&gt; .</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+f|</b>&gt; I have spend the last term on the DPL-Team and already then</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+b|</b>&gt; worked hard to achive more transparency, communication and openness</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+c|</b>&gt; within the project. New workmeetings take place this year and the</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+d|</b>&gt; project got more and better resources already. Next term I would</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+e|</b>&gt; continue those effords to make Debian a pleasent working environment,</li>
<li class="n1"> &lt;<b>+f|</b>&gt; colaborating in a purpose driven way.</li>
